						<summary>

						<p>On a slab set up in front of the Bharatēśvara temple.</p>						

						<p>1032 A.D.</p>						

						<p>This is dated Śaka 954, Āṅgirasa, Āshāḍha śu. 1, Sunday, corresponding to 1032, A.D., June 11.</p>						

						<p>It records a gift of land to the god Bharatēśvara. The gift land was purchased from the Two-Hundred <hi rend="italic">Mahājanas</hi> of Bharatāpura and was entrusted into their hands for protection.</p>						

						</summary>
